Brazil Central Bank Names Lopes, Marques for Board

-- B y   A n d r e   S o l i a n i
-- 
2011-02-16T11:15:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/brazil-central-bank-names-lopes-marques-for-board-update1-.html
  Brazil ’s central bank President
Alexandre Tombini recommended Altamir Lopes as  director  of
administration and Sidnei Correa Marques as director for
liquidation and surveillance of farm credit operations.  Lopes, 58, has been working as the head of the economic
research department at the central bank. He would replace
Anthero de Moraes Meirelles, who will become director of
supervision, the central bank said in an e-mailed statement.  Correa Marques, 57, has been head of the department of
financial system monitoring and information management at the
central bank and would replace Antonio Gustavo Matos do Vale,
who is leaving the bank.  Alvir Hoffmann is also leaving the central bank’s board.  The nominations must be approved by the Senate, the central
bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andre Soliani in Brasilia at 
 asoliani@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Laura Price at 
 lprice3@bloomberg.net  